# Next.js App Router — ClientPilot Conventions

## Server vs Client Components
- Default to **Server Components**. Add `"use client"` only when needed (hooks, browser events, Radix interactive state).
- Never import `lib/supabase/server.ts` or `lib/supabase/admin.ts` from a Client Component.

## Route Actions
- Server Actions live in `actions.ts` colocated next to the page they serve (`app/dashboard/settings/actions.ts`).
- Mark actions with `"use server"`. Validate inputs with `zod` before touching the DB.
- Return `{ error: string }` on failure, redirect on success.

## API Routes
- All webhook routes must set `export const runtime = "nodejs"` (Twilio, Meta, Stripe all require Node APIs).
- Webhook routes: read raw body with `req.text()` **before** any other parsing (Stripe requires raw body for signature).
- Return `NextResponse.json({ received: true }, { status: 200 })` from Stripe/Meta/Twilio even on no-op events — 
  returning 4xx causes retries.

## Route Structure
```
app/
  (auth)/login/          — public auth pages
  onboarding/            — post-signup wizard
  dashboard/             — protected, layout.tsx checks session
  admin/                 — internal admin, uses lib/admin-guard.ts
  api/
    twilio/webhook/      — Twilio WhatsApp inbound
    meta/webhook/        — Meta Cloud API inbound (GET verify + POST)
    stripe/webhook/      — Stripe events
    google/callback/     — OAuth return
    cron/followups/      — Vercel cron trigger
```

## Auth Guard
`app/dashboard/layout.tsx` and `app/admin/layout.tsx` redirect to `/login` if no session.
Do not add redundant session checks inside individual pages — trust the layout.
